dex_entries.sun: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.
dex_entries.moon: This Oricorio has sipped red nectar. Its passionate dance moves cause its enemies to combust in both body and mind.
dex_entries.ultrasun: It wins the hearts of its enemies with its passionate dancing and then uses the opening it creates to burn them up with blazing flames.
dex_entries.ultramoon: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.

dex_entries.sun: This Oricorio has sipped bright yellow nectar. Its bright, cheerful dance melts the hearts of its enemies.
dex_entries.moon: It creates an electric charge by rubbing its feathers together. It dances over to its enemies and delivers shocking electrical punches.
dex_entries.ultrasun: It lifts its opponents’ spirits with its cheerful dance moves. When they let their guard down, it electrocutes them with a jolt.
dex_entries.ultramoon: This Oricorio has drunk bright yellow nectar. When it sees someone looking glum, it will try to cheer them up with a dance.

dex_entries.sun: This Oricorio relaxes by swaying gently. This increases its psychic energy, which it then fires at its enemies.
dex_entries.moon: This Oricorio has sipped pink nectar. Its enemies’ hearts melt at the sight of its gently swaying hips.
dex_entries.ultrasun: It relaxes its opponents with its elegant dancing. When they let their guard down, it showers them with psychic energy.
dex_entries.ultramoon: This Oricorio has sipped pink nectar. It gets so caught up in its dancing that it sometimes doesn’t hear its Trainer’s orders.

dex_entries.sun: This Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. Its elegant, attractive dance will send the minds and hearts of its enemies to another world.
dex_entries.moon: It summons the dead with its dreamy dancing. From their malice, it draws power with which to curse its enemies.
dex_entries.ultrasun: It charms its opponents with its refined dancing. When they let their guard down, it places a curse on them that will bring on their demise.
dex_entries.ultramoon: This Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. Some dancers use its graceful, elegant dancing as inspiration.

dex_entries.sun: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.
dex_entries.moon: When properly raised from a young age, it will become a trustworthy partner that will absolutely never betray its Trainer.
dex_entries.ultrasun: The sharp rocks in its mane can cut like knives. Lycanroc wears its prey down by degrees before finishing them off.
dex_entries.ultramoon: The rocks in its mane are sharper than a knife. Fragments that break off are treasured as good luck charms.

from.name: Rockruff
from.method: Level 25, Nighttime, In Pokémon Moon Or Ultra Moon

dex_entries.sun: The more intimidating the opponent it faces, the more this Pokémon’s blood boils. It will attack with no regard for its own safety.
dex_entries.moon: It goads its enemies into attacking, withstands the hits, and in return, delivers a headbutt, crushing their bones with its rocky mane.
dex_entries.ultrasun: It has no problem ignoring orders it doesn’t like. It doesn’t seem to mind getting hurt at all—as long as it can finish off its opponent.
dex_entries.ultramoon: They live alone without forming packs. They will only listen to orders from Trainers who can draw out their true power.

dex_entries.ultrasun: Bathed in the setting sun of evening, Lycanroc has undergone a special kind of evolution. An intense fighting spirit underlies its calmness.
dex_entries.ultramoon: This strange form is the result of its evolving at dusk. It’s very rare in Alola.

dex_entries.sun: When it’s in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.
dex_entries.moon: It’s awfully weak and notably tasty, so everyone is always out to get it. As it happens, anyone trying to bully it receives a painful lesson.
dex_entries.ultrasun: They’re weak, so they move in schools. However, they can also often be seen all alone, having strayed from the school.
dex_entries.ultramoon: When it’s in a jam, its shining eyes attract others of its kind. The light from its eyes is visible almost 25 miles away.
dex_entries.sword: Individually, they’re incredibly weak. It’s by gathering up into schools that they’re able to confront opponents.
dex_entries.shield: When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.

dex_entries.sun: Weak Wishiwashi school together to concentrate their power. Their united force makes them the demon of the sea, feared near and far.
dex_entries.moon: At their appearance, even Gyarados will flee. When they team up to use Water Gun, its power exceeds that of Hydro Pump.
dex_entries.ultrasun: Wishiwashi assemble in this formation to face off against strong foes. It boasts a strength that earned it the name “demon of the sea.”
dex_entries.ultramoon: Called “demon of the sea” by some, when Wishiwashi are injured in battle and their numbers dwindle, they become a regular school.
dex_entries.sword: On their own, they’re very weak. But when Wishiwashi pool their power together in a school, they become a demon of the sea.
dex_entries.shield: When facing tough opponents, they get into formation. But if they get wounded in battle, they’ll scatter and become solitary again.

dex_entries.sun: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokémon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.
dex_entries.moon: Although its name was Type: Null at first, the boy who evolved it into this form gave it the name by which it is now known.
dex_entries.ultrasun: This is its form once it has awakened and evolved. Freed from its heavy mask, its speed is greatly increased.
dex_entries.ultramoon: Through the bond it formed with its Trainer, its will was strengthened, and it was able to destroy its control mask.
dex_entries.sword: A solid bond of trust between this Pokémon and its Trainer awakened the strength hidden within Silvally. It can change its type at will.
dex_entries.shield: The final factor needed to release this Pokémon’s true power was a strong bond with a Trainer it trusts.

dex_entries.sun: Originally making its home in the ozone layer, it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing its body grows too heavy.
dex_entries.moon: Strong impacts can knock it out of its shell. This Pokémon was born from mutated nanoparticles.
dex_entries.ultrasun: It lives in the ozone layer, where it becomes food for stronger Pokémon. When it tries to run away, it falls to the ground.
dex_entries.ultramoon: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.

dex_entries.sun: It eats dust in the atmosphere. The composition of the dust determines the color of its core.
dex_entries.moon: If its core stays exposed, it will soon die off. It’s possible that it may survive if it’s put into a Poké Ball quickly enough.
dex_entries.ultrasun: Places where Minior fall from the night sky are few and far between, with Alola being one of the precious few.
dex_entries.ultramoon: This is its form when its shell has fallen off. The color of its core depends on the materials that made up the food it ate.

dex_entries.sun: Reminiscent of the Ultra Beasts, this life-form, apparently asleep underground, is thought to have come from another world in ancient times.
dex_entries.moon: Light is apparently the source of its energy. It has an extraordinarily vicious disposition and is constantly firing off laser beams.
dex_entries.ultrasun: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It’s apparently from another world.
dex_entries.ultramoon: Light is the source of its energy. If it isn’t devouring light, impurities build up in it and on it, and Necrozma darkens and stops moving.
dex_entries.sword: It survives by absorbing light. After a long time spent slumbering underground, impurities accumulated within it, causing its body to darken.
dex_entries.shield: It needs light to survive, and it goes on a rampage seeking it out. Its laser beams will cut anything to pieces.

dex_entries.ultrasun: This is its form while it is devouring the light of Solgaleo. It pounces on foes and then slashes them with the claws on its four limbs and back.
dex_entries.ultramoon: This is Necrozma’s form while it’s absorbing the power of Solgaleo, making it extremely ferocious and impossible to control.
dex_entries.sword: When it dominates Solgaleo, it takes on this form. It’s a vicious Pokémon, mangling prey with its many claws—including those on its back.
dex_entries.shield: Necrozma has attached itself to Solgaleo. It siphons away its host’s limitless energy, exploiting that energy to fuel a rampage.

dex_entries.ultrasun: Lunala no longer has a will of its own. Now under the control of Necrozma, it continuously expels all of its energy.
dex_entries.ultramoon: This is its form while it’s devouring the light of Lunala. It grasps foes in its giant claws and rips them apart with brute force.
dex_entries.sword: Necrozma has subjugated Lunala entirely, forcing the unfortunate Pokémon to emit its light energy for Necrozma to consume.
dex_entries.shield: When Necrozma latches on to Lunala, it becomes vicious, seeing enemies everywhere it looks. It will burn the world with lasers.

dex_entries.ultrasun: This is its form when it has absorbed overwhelming light energy. It fires laser beams from all over its body.
dex_entries.ultramoon: The light pouring out from all over its body affects living things and nature, impacting them in various ways.

dex_entries.sun: This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.
dex_entries.moon: Its mechanized body is merely a vessel. Its true self is its Soul-Heart, an artificial soul.
dex_entries.ultrasun: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.
dex_entries.ultramoon: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

name_origin.shadow: dark area created by blocking out light

name_origin.cephalo-: of or relating to the head

dex_entries.letsgopikachu: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.
dex_entries.letsgoeevee: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.
dex_entries.sword: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.
dex_entries.shield: Centrifugal force is behind the punches of Melmetal’s heavy hex-nut arms. Melmetal is said to deliver the strongest punches of all Pokémon.
